import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['home_score'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Home Scores')
    plt.axvline(data['home_score'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['home_score'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Home Scores')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of home scores?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['score_difference'] = data['home_score'] - data['away_score']
    plt.hist(data['score_difference'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Score Difference')
    plt.axvline(data['score_difference'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['score_difference'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Score Difference')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of score difference?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_grouped = data.groupby('division')['score_difference'].mean()
    ax = data_grouped.plot(kind='bar', color='blue', legend=True)
    plt.title('What is the average score difference by division?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Division')
    plt.ylabel('Average Score Difference')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['home_score'])
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Home Score')
    plt.title('What is the trend of home scores over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Home Score'])
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
